      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "ci: add GitHub Pages deploy workflow for website",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Publishes the `website/` app through GitHub Pages at the canonical public URL, `https://voxcli.sh`.\n- Uses one Pages workflow with current action majors, deployment-only Pages/OIDC permissions, and manual recovery dispatch.\n- Builds from the Pages-configured base path, so custom-domain `/` and repository fallback `/vox/` assets both resolve correctly.\n- Fixes the preloader, favicon, canonical URL, and social-image paths; verifies the generated HTML, JS asset, and CNAME artifact.\n- Removes the unused Netlify and Vercel deployment configurations so GitHub Pages is the single hosting contract.\n\n## User impact\n\nThe merged Vox marketing site gains an owned deployment path and canonical URL instead of remaining only a buildable repository subproject. Changes under `website/` publish automatically after the deployment build, typecheck, and artifact checks pass.\n\n## Hosting contract\n\n- Canonical URL: `https://voxcli.sh`\n- Publisher: GitHub Pages, using GitHub Actions\n- Domain artifact: `website/public/CNAME`\n- Base path: supplied by `actions/configure-pages`, not hardcoded\n- Elevated permissions: `pages: write` and `id-token: write` on the deploy job only\n\n## Proof\n\nExact head: `c551514557f5ab36383b69e2be7c4905d5142bfc`\n\n- Root: frozen install, format/lint, typecheck, 61/61 tests, and production build pass.\n- Website: frozen install and typecheck pass.\n- Production builds for `/` and `/vox/` pass.\n- Deploy verifier confirms favicon/assets, preloader logo, CNAME, canonical URL, and social metadata for both bases.\n- `actionlint` passes for CI and deploy workflows.\n- Structured Codex autoreview: clean; no accepted/actionable findings.\n- GitHub CI and live deployment proof: pending this push.\n\n## Required repository setup\n\nGitHub Pages must use **GitHub Actions** as its source and `voxcli.sh` as its custom domain. DNS must point the apex at GitHub Pages before HTTPS/live proof can complete.\n",
